         MACRO                                                          00160000
.*                                                                      00170000
.* This macro handles the stack of DS modifications for use by the      00180000
.* DS macro, which replaces the assembler's DS instruction              00190000
.*                                                                      00200000
&LABEL   DSOVR &OPT,                   * Parameters are in &SYSLIST    *00210000
               &NEWNAM                 * New name for *NEWNAME option   00220000
.*                                                                      00230000
.* &LABEL mandatory, except when &OPT=*END                              00240000
.*        To specify an override for an unlabeled DS, specify the label 00250000
.*        of the last preceding labeled DS and the relative number of   00260000
.*        the unlabeled statement to be overridden. E.g.: LABEG+3,      00270000
.*        would  mean the third unlabeled DS after the DS with label    00280000
.*        LABEG.                                                        00290000
.* &OPT   specifies one of the following:                               00300000
.*        *END cancels all outstanding DSOVR requests                   00310000
.*        *SUPPRESS suppresses the definition of &LABEL                 00320000
.*        *NEWNAME changes the DS for &LABEL into one for &NEWNAM,      00330000
.*              i.e. Specify *NEWNAME,newname,parmstring                00340000
.*        Other values override the DS-operand string                   00350000
.* &NEWNAM Specifies the new name, if &OPT=*NEWNAME                     00360000
.*        &NEWNAM may optionally be followed by a parameter string      00370000
.*        If &NEWNAM specifies *NONAME the DS will become unlabeled     00380000
.* &SYSLIST Specifies an operand string, which replaces the complete    00390000
.*        operand string of the original DS statement.                  00400000
.*                                                                      00410000
